\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and its vector 
\begin_inset Formula $P=(p_{1},...,p_{s},...,p_{S})$
\end_inset

 of the probabilities of each consequences in 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Most of the time, one will take the set of consequences as a given, so that
 lottery 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 will be denoted by its vector 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

